/quickstart.title: Quickstart
/quickstart.content:
quickstart

guide working with color programmatically

what’s

can defined using different data types(arrays strings numbers plain objects) this allows us work almost any format flexibility how want define our color below are some examples listing all supported formats passing values their respective conversion functions:

import { num2rgb tohex } from 'huetifuljs'let cssnamedcolor = 'pink'let colornumber 5000let colorobject l: 50 c: 20 h: 40 mode: 'lch' }let colorobjectwithalpha alpha: 05 arrcolor ['rgb' 120 80 50]let arrcolorwithalpha 01]// converting css named colors hexconsolelog(tohex(cssnamedcolor))// #ffc0cb// number rgb objectconsolelog(num2rgb(colornumber true))// #001388// object 6 character hex (without alpha value)consolelog(tohex(colorobject))// #956d62// property 8 code (including channel)consolelog(tohex(colorobjectwithalpha))// #956d6280// array channel codeconsolelog(tohex(arrcolor))// #785032// channel) hexconsolelog(tohex(arrcolorwithalpha))//#7850321a
< href="https://culorijsorg/colorspaces" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">see here expected ranges href="https://prjctimggithubio/huetiful/modules/convertershtml" noreferrer">more converter functions page

tailwindcss colors

starting point library comes along default tailwindcss palette included helps get started easier when ’re href="https://prjctimggithubio/huetiful/modules/generatorshtml" noreferrer">palette such hueshift() earthtone()

tailwind accessed two wrapper functions tailwindcolors colors that both take same parameters takes once while curried here’s example showing differences between class="languagejs"> import tailwindcolors "huetifuljs";// pass red target hue// returns function called optional value parameterlet tailwindcolors("red");consolelog(red());// [ '#fef2f2' '#fee2e2' '#fecaca' '#fca5a5' '#f87171' '#ef4444' '#dc2626' '#b91c1c' '#991b1b' '#7f1d1d']consolelog(red(100));// '#fee2e2'consolelog(red('900'));// '#7f1d1d' ////// colors() //////// builtin parameter 'all' specified valuelet all300 colors("all" 300);consolelog(all300)//[ '#cbd5e1' '#d1d5db' '#d4d4d8' '#d4d4d4' '#d6d3d1' '#fdba74' '#fcd34d' '#fde047' '#bef264' '#86efac' '#6ee7b7' '#5eead4' '#7dd3fc' '#93c5fd' '#c4b5fd' '#d8b4fe' '#f0abfc' '#f9a8d4' '#fda4af']let colors("red");consolelog(red);// '#7f1d1d']let red100 colors("red" 100);consolelog(red100)// #fee2e2

working arrays color

sort filter like saturationlightness even contrast!
here filtering sorting functions colors:

sorting colors

by relative luminance wcag 20 formula

filtering hue angle uses jch colorspace because its perceptual uniformity href="https://tympanusnet/codrops/2021/12/07/coloringwithcodeprogrammaticapproachdesign/" noreferrer">george francis explains phenomena detail here

< href="https://prjctimggithubio/huetiful/modules/sortbyhtml" more about types other functions

palette generators

few simple generator included library one favourites hueshift ( becomes lighter shifts darker down )

< id="predicatesâï¸">predicates

cool warm achromatic (grayscale) chromatic though easy tell apart visually they’re displayed screen bit confusing code determine gray :

import isachromatic "huetifuljs";import formathex8 interpolate samples "culori"isachromatic('pink')// falselet 'pink'];consolelog(map(sample isachromatic));// [false false falsefalse]isachromatic('gray')// true// culori's demonstrate example// create interpolation black whitelet f interpolate(["black" "white"]);// then 12 evenly spaced them `t` param required interpolating function// lastly convert brevity (otherwise objects fine too)let grays map(samples(12) (c) => formathex8(f(c)));consolelog(map(grays last false can't categorize white achromatic// true true false]
here’s example check cool predicate iscool "#00c000"];consolelog(iscool(sample[0]));// falseconsolelog(map(sample iscool));// true]another use case would method filter collection removing passed predicate following iswarm only colors:

/about-colorspaces.title: About colorspaces
/about-colorspaces.content:
about colorspaces

this library makes use predefined colorspaces provided by culori information about expected channel ranges supported other related how handles them < href="https://culorijsorg/colorspaces/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">can found here

channel range normalization

because culori defines its may feel unintuitive let’s say example pass rgb values [01] since most developers are familiar [0255] range which isn’t compatible with will return unexpected results:

import { formathex } from 'culori';// culorilet colora = r: 1 g: 05 b: 005 mode: 'rgb' };consolelog(formathex(colora));// #ff800d// also valid colorb 100 58 4351 };consolelog(formathex(colorb));// #ffffff
note that colorb returned pure white this same color token correct tohex converter generic:

utility treat any greater than 1 contrast way such scenario where just clamp ranges formula very simple: channel / 255 give us our value range behaviour applies tokens passed arrays
